{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZbkfrhCRMUebRcgh37pPW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE.md\n     2→\n     3→This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4→\n     5→## Project Overview\n     6→\n     7→Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     8→environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\n     9→tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n    10→\n    11→**Language:** Go\n    12→\n    13→**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n    14→\n    15→## Architecture\n    16→\n    17→Three binaries from one Go module:\n    18→\n    19→- **`cloche`** (CLI) — Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n    20→- **`cloched`** (Daemon) — Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Executes host workflows (`host.cloche`) step by step on the host machine, dispatching container workflow runs as needed.\n    21→- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) — Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n    22→\n    23→Hexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\n    24→interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\n    25→them (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n    26→\n    27→```\n    28→cmd/\n    29→  cloche/           # CLI client\n    30→  cloched/          # Daemon\n    31→  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\n    32→internal/\n    33→  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n    34→  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n    35→  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n    36→  host/             # Host workflow executor (runs steps on host machine)\n    37→```\n    38→\n    39→## Workflow DSL\n    40→\n    41→Steps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    42→built-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    43→\n    44→## Project Layout\n    45→\n    46→Cloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    47→\n    48→```\n    49→my-project/\n    50→├── .cloche/"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"8734a279-8744-4e80-be9e-f4f7ea56e421"}
