{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B8wAbK75YxMqkDp7j9xGgM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Design: `cloche init`\n     2→\n     3→## Purpose\n     4→\n     5→Scaffold a Cloche project in the current directory so a user can go from\n     6→zero to `cloche run` with minimal setup.\n     7→\n     8→## CLI Interface\n     9→\n    10→```\n    11→cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--image <base-image>]\n    12→```\n    13→\n    14→| Flag | Default | Description |\n    15→|------|---------|-------------|\n    16→| `--workflow` | `develop` | Workflow name; creates `<name>.cloche` |\n    17→| `--image` | `ubuntu:24.04` | Base Docker image for Dockerfile |\n    18→\n    19→No flags required. Bare `cloche init` works with sensible defaults.\n    20→\n    21→## Generated Files\n    22→\n    23→```\n    24→.\n    25→├── <workflow>.cloche\n    26→├── Dockerfile\n    27→└── prompts/\n    28→    ├── implement.md\n    29→    └── fix.md\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→### Workflow (`develop.cloche`)\n    33→\n    34→Generic 3-step: implement, test, fix loop. Placeholder `make test` command.\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→workflow \"<name>\" {\n    38→  step implement {\n    39→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    40→    results = [success, fail]\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  step test {\n    44→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    45→    results = [success, fail]\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  step fix {\n    49→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    50→    max_attempts = \"2\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"5d35b873-49ca-49fc-b2d1-01c5821e4058"}
