{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011fU5sxZgzs9qXf2LvpxDtv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Workflows\n     2→\n     3→Cloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n     4→\n     5→## Workflow Locations\n     6→\n     7→Cloche distinguishes two workflow locations based on the file they live in:\n     8→\n     9→**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) — Run inside a Docker\n    10→container via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type. These are the\n    11→standard workflows for coding tasks.\n    12→\n    13→**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — Runs on the host machine as the daemon\n    14→process. Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow` step type\n    15→dispatches a container workflow run and waits for it to complete. This is the extension\n    16→point for custom orchestration strategies.\n    17→\n    18→The convention is enforced at parse time: a `workflow_name` step in a container workflow\n    19→file is a parse error.\n    20→\n    21→## Concepts\n    22→\n    23→| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    24→|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    25→| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    26→| step     | A unit of work (inferred: `prompt` = agent, `run` = script)        |\n    27→| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    28→| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step, with optional output mappings |\n    29→| done     | Built-in terminal step — successful completion                     |\n    30→| abort    | Built-in terminal step — failure with error reporting              |\n    31→\n    32→## Step Types\n    33→\n    34→Step type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n    35→\n    36→**agent** (has `prompt`) — Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\n    37→to the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\n    38→container. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    39→\n    40→**script** (has `run`) — Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\n    41→any deterministic check. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    42→\n    43→**workflow** (has `workflow_name`) — Dispatches a named container workflow run and blocks\n    44→until it completes. Only available in host workflows (`host.cloche`).\n    45→\n    46→A step with more than one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`, or none of them, is a\n    47→parse error.\n    48→\n    49→## DSL Syntax\n    50→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"d57f96bb-7d32-4b17-83eb-919c1da75346"}
