{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AJkkNqYtjEvAyPufazTYc9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Docker Base Image Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The default Dockerfile generated by `cloche init` builds `cloche-agent` from the cloche\n     9→Go source inside the image. This only works for the cloche project itself (which has the\n    10→source available). For any other project, the template is broken out of the box.\n    11→\n    12→The root `Dockerfile` (used by the cloche project's own `.cloche/`) makes the same\n    13→mistake, and is also unnecessarily large (based on `golang:1.25` for the final stage).\n    14→\n    15→## Solution\n    16→\n    17→A `cloche-base` image: a minimal Debian-slim image with `git` and `cloche-agent`\n    18→pre-installed. Projects start from this image and add their own tooling on top.\n    19→\n    20→Using `cloche-base` is **not required** — projects may use any Dockerfile they like.\n    21→\n    22→---\n    23→\n    24→## `cloche-base` image contents\n    25→\n    26→Built from `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` in the cloche repo.\n    27→\n    28→| Component | Why |\n    29→|-----------|-----|\n    30→| `debian:12-slim` | Small, stable, widely compatible |\n    31→| `git` | Required by `cloche-agent` for branch/commit operations |\n    32→| `ca-certificates` | TLS for any outbound requests agents make |\n    33→| `cloche-agent` binary | The in-container workflow executor |\n    34→| `agent` user | Unprivileged user; workdir `/workspace` owned by `agent` |\n    35→\n    36→**Not included:** Node.js, npm, claude-code, language runtimes, build tools. These are\n    37→project-specific and belong in the project's own Dockerfile.\n    38→\n    39→### `docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n    40→\n    41→```dockerfile\n    42→FROM golang:1.25 AS builder\n    43→WORKDIR /src\n    44→COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n    45→RUN go mod download\n    46→COPY . .\n    47→RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    48→\n    49→FROM debian:12-slim\n    50→RUN apt-get update \\"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"c07c31b2-122d-4eb8-9740-16778e60be6a"}
