{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012epjQe4jiFDSKQ49cH1EjH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my comprehensive review of all the files, here's a detailed summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. **internal/host/task.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Purpose:** Implements task assignment from external task trackers.\n\n**New Types:**\n- `Task` - Represents a work item with `ID`, `Title`, and `Description` fields\n- `TaskAssigner` - Interface for listing available tasks (`ListTasks(ctx, projectDir) ([]Task, error)`)\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner` - Concrete implementation that executes a shell command and parses JSON output\n\n**Key Behavior:**\n- Executes a configurable shell command (e.g., `bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh`)\n- Parses JSON array output to extract task objects\n- Handles empty arrays and empty output gracefully (returns nil, no error)\n- Uses `MainWorktreeDir(projectDir)` to run commands from the main git worktree\n\n---\n\n### 2. **internal/host/task_test.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Test Coverage:**\n- JSON array parsing with complete task objects\n- Empty array handling\n- Empty output handling\n- Command execution failures\n- Invalid JSON error handling\n- Partial field objects (only `id` required)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **internal/host/executor.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Fields in `Executor` struct:**\n- `TaskID string` - Optional task ID assigned by the daemon loop\n\n**New Environment Variables Passed to Scripts:**\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - The daemon-assigned task ID (only if set)\n\n**New Function:**\n- `scriptDir()` - Returns `MainDir` if set, otherwise `ProjectDir` (scripts execute from here)\n\n**Modified Functions:**\n- `executeScript()` - Now passes `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var to shell commands\n- All step types now use `scriptDir()` instead of `ProjectDir` for execution directory\n\n**New Exported Utility Function:**\n- `MainWorktreeDir(projectDir string) string` - Returns the path of the main git worktree using `git worktree list --porcelain`\n\n---\n\n### 4. **internal/host/executor_test.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Tests:**\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_TaskIDEnvVar` - Verifies `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var is passed when set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_NoTaskID` - Verifies env var is empty when not set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_UsesMainDir` - Verifies scripts execute from `MainDir` when set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_MainDirOverridesProjectDir` - MainDir takes precedence\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_FallsBackToProjectDir` - Falls back when MainDir is empty\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_ProjectDirEnvVar` - Verifies `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` always points to ProjectDir\n- `TestMainWorktreeDir_NonGitDir` - Tests fallback for non-git directories\n- `TestMainWorktreeDir_WithWorktree` - Tests resolution with actual git worktrees\n- `TestExecutor_AgentStep_*` - Multiple tests for host-based agent execution\n- `TestRunner_WithTaskID` - Verifies task ID propagation through host runner\n- `TestRunner_HostWorkflow_AgentStep*` - Tests agent steps in host workflows\n\n---\n\n### 5. **internal/host/loop.go** (NEW FILE - Orchestration Loop)\n**Purpose:** Manages continuous orchestration of host workflow runs with task assignment.\n\n**New Constants:**\n- `defaultMaxConcurrent = 1`\n- `defaultDedupTimeout = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `idlePollInterval = 30 * time.Second`\n- `capacityPollInterval = 5 * time.Second`\n\n**New Types:**\n- `LoopConfig` - Configuration struct with fields:\n  - `ProjectDir string`\n  - `MaxConcurrent int` - Max concurrent runs (default: 1)\n  - `StaggerDelay time.Duration` - Delay between launching runs\n  - `DedupTimeout time.Duration` - How long to suppress reassignment of same task ID (default: 5 min)\n  \n- `RunFunc` - Signature: `func(ctx, projectDir, taskID) (*RunResult, error)`\n\n- `Loop` - Orchestration loop manager with:\n  - `config LoopConfig`\n  - `runner RunFunc`\n  - `store ports.RunStore`\n  - `assigner TaskAssigner` (optional)\n  - Dedup map to prevent task reassignment within timeout window\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `NewLoop(cfg, store, runFn) *Loop` - Creates loop with defaults\n- `SetTaskAssigner(a TaskAssigner)` - Configure task assignment\n- `Start()` / `Stop()` / `Running() bool` - Lifecycle management\n- `pickTask() (string, bool)` - Selects assignable task from list, filters dedup window, returns task ID\n- `countActiveHostRuns() int` - Counts running/pending host runs for the project\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- Maintains up to `MaxConcurrent` active runs\n- Ramps up immediately on success (no backoff)\n- Backs off with `idlePollInterval` (30s) on failure\n- Supports task deduplication with expiring time window\n- Staggered launch delays to avoid race conditions\n- Goroutine-based concurrent execution\n\n---\n\n### 6. **internal/host/loop_test.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Start/Stop lifecycle\n- Ramp-up on successful runs\n- Double-start idempotency\n- Task assignment and passing to runner\n- Task deduplication prevention\n- Dedup expiration\n- Backoff when no tasks available\n- Backward compatibility (no task assigner = empty taskID)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **internal/host/runner.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Field in `Runner` struct:**\n- `TaskID string` - Optional task ID assigned by daemon loop\n\n**New Method:**\n- `RunWithID(ctx, projectDir, orchRunID) (*RunResult, error)` - Run with specific run ID\n\n**Modified `Run()` Method:**\n- Now delegates to `RunWithID()` with generated ID\n\n**Changes:**\n- Passes `TaskID` to `Executor` during setup\n- Executor uses it to populate `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n\n**New Type:**\n- `RunResult` - Contains `RunID string` and `State domain.RunState`\n\n---\n\n### 8. **internal/config/config.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Fields in `OrchestrationConfig` struct:**\n- `Concurrency int` (renamed from implicit field) - Max concurrent runs\n- `StaggerSeconds float64` - Delay between launching runs\n- `ListTasksCommand string` - Shell command to list open tasks (JSON array output)\n- `DedupSeconds float64` - Dedup window for task assignment (default: 300s/5min)\n\n**Default Values Added:**\n- `Concurrency: 1`\n- `StaggerSeconds: 1.0`\n\n---\n\n### 9. **internal/adapters/grpc/server.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Field in `ClocheServer` struct:**\n- `loops map[string]*host.Loop` - Maps project_dir -> orchestration loop instance\n\n**New RPC Endpoints:**\n\n1. **`EnableLoop(ctx, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error)`**\n   - Enables orchestration loop for a project\n   - Creates `Loop` with config from `config.Load(projectDir).Orchestration`\n   - Configures `ScriptTaskAssigner` if `ListTasksCommand` is set\n   - Starts the loop immediately\n   - Handles:\n     - `MaxConcurrent` override in request\n     - Stagger delay from config\n     - Dedup timeout from config\n     - Task assignment setup with logging\n\n2. **`DisableLoop(ctx, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error)`**\n   - Stops and removes orchestration loop for a project\n   - Stops the loop's background goroutine\n\n**Modified Methods:**\n\n- **`Shutdown(ctx, req)`** - Now stops all orchestration loops before shutting down\n\n**Integration Points:**\n- `EnableLoop` creates `host.Runner` instances with task assignment support\n- Runner's `TaskID` comes from loop's task selection\n- Loops are stored per project for management\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Behavioral Changes\n\n1. **Host Workflow Execution**: Host workflows can now be orchestrated continuously with the daemon picking up work from external task trackers.\n\n2. **Task Assignment**: The daemon can query a shell script to get available tasks and pass them to workflow runs via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable.\n\n3. **Deduplication**: Tasks within the dedup timeout window (default 5 minutes) won't be reassigned, preventing concurrent work on the same task.\n\n4. **Concurrency Control**: Multiple host workflow runs can execute concurrently (configurable, default 1) with staggered launches to avoid race conditions.\n\n5. **Main Worktree Support**: Scripts in host workflows can execute from the main git worktree (non-linked branch) instead of linked worktree directories.\n\n6. **Configuration**: New `orchestration` section in `config.toml` controls concurrency, stagger delay, task source, and dedup window."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9bf9ec0a48e3a18c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64721\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 26655</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"09a68282-a97e-4425-8989-09b75b241357","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files completely and summarize what each one does, focusing on new types, functions, config keys, CLI flags, and any behavioral changes:\n\n1. internal/host/task.go (new file)\n2. internal/host/task_test.go (new file)\n3. internal/host/executor.go (modified)\n4. internal/host/executor_test.go (modified)\n5. internal/host/loop.go (modified)\n6. internal/host/loop_test.go (modified)\n7. internal/host/runner.go (modified)\n8. internal/config/config.go (modified)\n9. internal/adapters/grpc/server.go (modified)\n\nFor each file, note:\n- New exported types/functions\n- New config keys or environment variables\n- New gRPC endpoints or CLI flags\n- Changed behavior in existing functions\n- Any constants or default values","agentId":"a9bf9ec0a48e3a18c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my comprehensive review of all the files, here's a detailed summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. **internal/host/task.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Purpose:** Implements task assignment from external task trackers.\n\n**New Types:**\n- `Task` - Represents a work item with `ID`, `Title`, and `Description` fields\n- `TaskAssigner` - Interface for listing available tasks (`ListTasks(ctx, projectDir) ([]Task, error)`)\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner` - Concrete implementation that executes a shell command and p