{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of all documentation files found in the repository.\n\n## Documentation Files Summary\n\nI've found all documentation files in the repository. Here's a comprehensive list organized by category:\n\n### Root-Level Documentation\n\n1. **`/workspace/CLAUDE.md`** - Project guidance for Claude Code. Covers project overview, three-binary architecture (cloche CLI, cloched daemon, cloche-agent), hexagonal architecture, workflow DSL, and project layout with `.cloche/` directory structure.\n\n2. **`/workspace/README.md`** - High-level system introduction. Explains what Cloche is (a system for grow-coding applications), core features (containerized environments, workflow syntax, validated code, self-evolving tooling), container isolation strategy, and references to detailed docs.\n\n3. **`/workspace/PROJECT.md`** - Next features and roadmap. Covers orchestration needs, indicator lights/dashboard, web dashboard, log capture, and container deletion strategies.\n\n4. **`/workspace/AGENTS.md`** - Agent instructions for issue tracking with beads (bd), quick reference commands, and mandatory workflow for landing sessions (file issues, run quality gates, update status, push to remote).\n\n### Installation & Usage Documentation\n\n5. **`/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`** - Installation guide covering prerequisites (Docker, Git, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY), build from source instructions, and `go install` method.\n\n6. **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`** - Core usage documentation. Covers workflow concepts (workflow, step, result, wiring, terminals), DSL syntax, step configuration (prompt, run, workflow_name, results, timeout, max_attempts, output, overrides).\n\n7. **`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`** - Comprehensive workflow reference. Explains workflow locations (container vs. host workflows), step types (agent, script, workflow), DSL syntax with examples, and wiring conventions.\n\n### System Design Documents (in `/workspace/docs/plans/`)\n\n8. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`** - MVP architecture describing three binaries, cloche CLI subcommands, cloched daemon responsibilities, cloche-agent runtime, domain types, and storage/adapter patterns.\n\n9. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`** - Detailed implementation roadmap with phases (Foundation, DSL Parser, Engine, Agent Binary, Daemon, CLI) and specific task breakdowns.\n\n10. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md`** - Result protocol design using `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` stdout markers, fallback behavior based on exit codes, fanout/collect patterns for parallel branches.\n\n11. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md`** - Implementation details for edge selection (reading result names from README, creating empty result directories).\n\n12. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`** - `cloche init` CLI design with flags for `--workflow` and `--image`, generated file structure, and default workflow template.\n\n13. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md`** - Implementation plan for cloche init command, file generation, and template content.\n\n14. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`** - Self-evolution system architecture using ACE framework, multi-stage pipeline (Collector, Classifier, Reflector) for automatically improving prompts and workflows based on run history.\n\n15. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`** - Implementation details for evolution system stages, change tracking, and audit trails.\n\n16. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md`** - Directory structure reorganization (`.cloche/` subdirectory), daemon-side result extraction using docker cp, and `poll` command for blocking until run completion.\n\n17. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-impl.md`** - Implementation details for subdirectory layout and polling mechanism.\n\n18. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`** - Future features including orchestration, indicator lights, web dashboard, and container deletion.\n\n19. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md`** - Per-step timeout configuration using DSL syntax (e.g., `timeout = \"45m\"`), engine-level timeout handling, and timeout behavior.\n\n20. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md`** - Updated cloche init design with workflow templates and file generation.\n\n21. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md`** - Docker base image design creating a minimal `cloche-base` image with Git, TLS certificates, and cloche-agent pre-installed for use by projects.\n\n22. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`** - Project settings file renamed from `.cloche/config` to `.cloche/config.toml` with TOML syntax and configuration sections for orchestration and evolution.\n\n23. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`** - Host workflow system (`host.cloche`) for custom orchestration strategies on the host machine, introducing workflow dispatch steps.\n\n24. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** - Web UI project pages showing orchestrator control, project info, workflow visualization, and health indicators.\n\n25. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`** - Project versioning system using `.cloche/version` file to track evolution cycle count.\n\n26. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md`** - Output mapping on wires for passing structured data between steps using expressions like `output.field` and `output[N].key` in DSL.\n\n### Example Project Documentation\n\n27. **`/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/README.md`** - Ruby calculator example documentation\n28. **`/workspace/examples/gemini-browser/DESIGN.md`** - Gemini browser example design documentation\n29. **`/workspace/examples/mini-redis/DESIGN.md`** - Mini-Redis example design documentation\n\nAll files listed above are legitimate documentation covering system architecture, configuration, workflows, host executor behavior, design decisions, and implementation plans for the Cloche system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5ebb7da0bd9021cc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32365\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 30700</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"47829077-20c2-43f0-b68e-4dd6452bfc0e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all documentation files in this repository. Look for:\n1. All .md files in docs/ directory (recursively)\n2. Any other .md files at root level or in other directories that might contain documentation about the system architecture, configuration, workflows, or host executor\n\nFor each documentation file found, provide its path and a brief summary of what it covers (read the first ~50 lines to understand the topic).","agentId":"a5ebb7da0bd9021cc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of all documentation files found in the repository.\n\n## Documentation Files Summary\n\nI've found all documentation files in the repository. Here's a comprehensive list organized by category:\n\n### Root-Level Documentation\n\n1. **`/workspace/CLAUDE.md`** - Project guidance for Claude Code. Covers project overview, three-binary architecture (cloche CLI, cloched daemon, cloche-agent), hexagonal architecture, workflow DSL, and project layout with `.cloche/` directory structure.\n\n2. **`/workspace/README.md`** - High-level system introduction. Explains what Cloche is (a system for grow-coding applications), core features (containerized environments, workflow syntax, validated code, self-evolving tooling), container isolation strategy, and references to detailed docs.\n\n3. **`/workspace/PROJECT.md`** - Next features and roadmap. Covers orchestration needs, indicator lights/dashboard, web dashboard, log capture, and container deletion strategies.\n\n4. **`/workspace/AGENTS.md`** - Agent instructions for issue tracking with beads (bd), quick reference commands, and mandatory workflow for landing sessions (file issues, run quality gates, update status, push to remote).\n\n### Installation & Usage Documentation\n\n5. **`/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`** - Installation guide covering prerequisites (Docker, Git, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY), build from source instructions, and `go install` method.\n\n6. **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`** - Core usage documentation. Covers workflow concepts (workflow, step, result, wiring, terminals), DSL syntax, step configuration (prompt, run, workflow_name, results, timeout, max_attempts, output, overrides).\n\n7. **`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`** - Comprehensive workflow reference. Explains workflow locations (container vs. host workflows), step types (agent, script, workflow), DSL syntax with examples, and wiring conventions.\n\n### System Design Documents (in `/workspace/docs/plans/`)\n\n8. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`** - MVP architecture describing three binaries, cloche CLI subcommands, cloched daemon responsibilities, cloche-agent runtime, domain types, and storage/adapter patterns.\n\n9. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`** - Detailed implementation roadmap with phases (Foundation, DSL Parser, Engine, Agent Binary, Daemon, CLI) and specific task breakdowns.\n\n10. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md`** - Result protocol design using `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` stdout markers, fallback behavior based on exit codes, fanout/collect patterns for parallel branches.\n\n11. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md`** - Implementation details for edge selection (reading result names from README, creating empty result directories).\n\n12. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`** - `cloche init` CLI design with flags for `--workflow` and `--image`, generated file structure, and default workflow template.\n\n13. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md`** - Implementation plan for cloche init command, file generation, and template content.\n\n14. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`** - Self-evolution system architecture using ACE framework, multi-stage pipeline (Collector, Classifier, Reflector) for automatically improving prompts and workflows based on run history.\n\n15. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`** - Implementation details for evolution system stages, change tracking, and audit trails.\n\n16. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md`** - Directory structure reorganization (`.cloche/` subdirectory), daemon-side result extraction using docker cp, and `poll` command for blocking until run completion.\n\n17. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-impl.md`** - Implementation details for subdirectory layout and polling mechanism.\n\n18. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`** - Future features including orchestration, indicator lights, web dashboard, and container deletion.\n\n19. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md`** - Per-step timeout configuration using DSL syntax (e.g., `timeout = \"45m\"`), engine-level timeout handling, and timeout behavior.\n\n20. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md`** - Updated cloche init design with workflow templates and file generation.\n\n21. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md`** - Docker base image design creating a minimal `cloche-base` image with Git, TLS certificates, and cloche-agent pre-installed for use by projects.\n\n22. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`** - Project settings file renamed from `.cloche/config` to `.cloche/config.toml` with TOML syntax and configuration sections for orchestration and evolution.\n\n23. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`** - Host workflow system (`host.cloche`) for custom orchestration strategies on the host machine, introducing workflow dispatch steps.\n\n24. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** - Web UI project pages showing orchestrator control, project info, workflow visualization, and health indicators.\n\n25. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`** - Project versioning system using `.cloche/version` file to track evolution cycle count.\n\n26. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md`** - Output mapping on wires for passing structured data between steps using expressions like `output.field` and `output[N].key` in DSL.\n\n### Example Project Documentation\n\n27. **`/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/README.md`** - Ruby calculator example documentation\n28. **`/workspace/examples/gemini-browser/DESIGN.md`** - Gemini browser example design documentation\n29. **`/workspace/examples/mini-redis/DESIGN.md`** - Mini-Redis example design documentation\n\nAll files listed above are legitimate documentation covering system architecture, configuration, workflows, host executor behavior, design decisions, and implementation plans for the Cloche system."}],"totalDurationMs":30700,"totalTokens":32365,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4479,"cache_read_input_tokens":26254,"output_tokens":1626,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4479},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
